stylometry: The data mining method we used was data clustering. We used it to group 49 United States cities according to demographics. We used the squared distances to group the data. The squared distances function figures out an average then figures out how far each piece of data is from the average. This is essentially how the data is clustered.  We also found the minimum and ran evolutionary solver to find the sum of squared distances. This allowed to data to be clustered by being assigned an index number. For example, we had 4 clusters so in the index column of every piece of data there was an assigned index number (1-4). By doing this we were able to cluster the states according to precentage of nationality.  This data could be used by businesses who are concerned with finding their target market which may be a certain demographic.
